HEADWORD: Mantra
<hw>Man"tra</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Skr.]</ety>
<def>A prayer; an invocation; a religious formula; a charm.</def>
<mark>[India]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Among the Hindoos each caste and tribe has a
<xex>mantra</xex> peculiar to itself; as, the <xex>mantra</xex> of the
Brahmans.</note> <rj><au>Balfour (Cyc. of India).</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mantrap</ent>⟦br⟧
